<subSubSection lastPageId="2" pageId="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1817,2022]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="2" pageId="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1817,1842]" pageId="1">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(based on 
<bibRefCitation author="Leistikow" box="[417,621,1817,1842]" pageId="1" refString="Leistikow, A. (2000 b) A new genus of Oniscidea from South America and a phylogenetic analysis of related genera (Crustacea: Isopoda: Philosciidae). Contributions to Zoology, The Hague, 69, 179 - 196." type="journal article" year="2000" yearSuffix="b">Leistikow 2000b</bibRefCitation>
). Species small, up to 
<quantity box="[919,1015,1817,1842]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="1" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
in length. Smooth tergal surface. Cephalothorax with linea supraantennalis; linea frontalis thin or absent; slight lateral lobes present; eyes with at most 8 ommatidia. Molar penicil of mandible with one prominent branch and up to four smaller ones. Mesal endite of first maxilla with two slender penicils; lateral endite bearing 4+4 or 5 teeth with inner set cleft. Maxilliped endite with one or two teeth caudally and knob-like “penicil” rostrally. Ornamental sensory spine of carpus of pereopod 1 with serrate double-fringe. Pereopods with inner claw of dactylus short and dactylar seta simple. Coxal plates I–VII with 
<emphasis box="[208,386,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="2">noduli laterales</emphasis>
(on coxal plate IV, 
<emphasis box="[608,697,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="2">nodulus</emphasis>
inserted more dorsally); coxal plates II with a spiny prolongation directed backward. Pleopods lacking respiratory areas; male pleopod 1 endopodite with apex bent laterally and with 3–4 lateral teeth directed proximally. Uropod protopodite grooved and endopodite inserting proximally relative to exopodite.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
